TITLE: Creating a Remote Component wrapper for React
DESCRIPTION: Creates a React wrapper component around a custom element using createRemoteComponent(). This wrapper provides proper TypeScript type support and correctly maps props to attributes, properties, or event listeners.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Shopify/remote-dom/blob/main/packages/react/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {createRoot} from 'react-dom/client';
import {createRemoteComponent} from '@remote-dom/react';

const MyElementComponent = createRemoteComponent('my-element', MyElement);

createRoot(document.querySelector('#root')).render(
  <MyElementComponent label="Hello, world!" />,
);
```

