TITLE: Initializing DOMRemoteReceiver in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Creates a DOMRemoteReceiver instance and connects it to the document body. This allows custom elements created in the remote environment to be attached to the body element.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Shopify/remote-dom/blob/main/packages/core/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {DOMRemoteReceiver} from '@remote-dom/core/receivers';

const receiver = new DOMRemoteReceiver();

// Any custom elements created in the remote environment will
// be attached to the `body` element.
receiver.connect(document.body);
```

