TITLE: Fetching Remote Element State with RemoteReceiver.get() in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use RemoteReceiver.get() to fetch the latest state of a remote element that has been received from the remote environment. It shows that calling get() on the root element returns the root itself.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Shopify/remote-dom/blob/main/packages/core/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_22

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import {RemoteReceiver} from '@remote-dom/core/receivers';

const receiver = new RemoteReceiver();

receiver.get(receiver.root) === receiver.root; // true
```

