TITLE: Mapping custom element events to React props
DESCRIPTION: Creates a React wrapper component that maps the 'expand' event from a custom element to an 'onExpand' prop in React using the createRemoteComponent() helper.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Shopify/remote-dom/blob/main/packages/react/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {createRemoteComponent} from '@remote-dom/preact';

const Card = createRemoteComponent('ui-card', CardElement, {
  eventProps: {
    onExpand: {event: 'expand'},
  },
});

render(
  <Card
    onExpand={() => {
      console.log('Card expanded!');
    }}
  >
    This is the body of the card.
  </Card>,
  document.querySelector('#root'),
);
```

