TITLE: Using slotted children in React components
DESCRIPTION: Uses createRemoteComponent() to map slotted children to React element props, allowing for cleaner composition of custom elements in React.
SOURCE: https://github.com/Shopify/remote-dom/blob/main/packages/react/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {createRoot} from 'react-dom/client';
import {createRemoteComponent} from '@remote-dom/react';

const Card = createRemoteComponent('ui-card', CardElement);
const Text = createRemoteComponent('ui-text', TextElement);

createRoot(document.querySelector('#root')).render(
  <Card header={<Text>Hello, world!</Text>}>
    This is the body of the card.
  </Card>,
);
```

